			<h1>STUDENTS</h1>
		</div>
		<div class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">
			<p class="right_msg" text-align="justify">
				
					<b>Who can participate as a student in Online UWC?</b><br />
					You can sign up for one of our 5 week long Online UWC courses if you are 14-20 years old. If you are younger, you can still review some of our <a href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC0uvvvnUly2dQVesT2pBu8Q">past video lectures</a> that have already taken place, but you will not be able to sign up to be a student. If you are over 20 and have graduated from a UWC and/or a university or college, get in touch with us about becoming a mentor by reaching out to hanna[at]onlineuwc.org (see more about what this involves in the Mentors section below).
					<br /><br />
					<b>Is this a UWC short course?</b><br />
					Yes, this is a UWC <a href="http://www.uwc.org/uwc_education/short_programmes/">short course</a> recognised by and run in affiliation with the UWC International Office (IO).
					<br /><br />
					<b>Does it matter where I live?</b><br />
					We are offering the Online UWC September-November 2014 5-week course to young people in the following regions (in three time zones, you can pick the time zone that works best for you):<br />
					Europe, Middle East and Africa (with live lectures and group sessions at 6pm London time)<br />
					Asia and the Pacific (with live lectures and group sessions at 7pm Hong Kong time)<br />
					Americas (with live lectures and group sessions at 6pm New York time)
					<br /><br />
					<b>I’m worried that my English isn’t good enough. Will this be a problem?</b><br />
					Not at all. There will be participants who are native-English speakers and participants who are native-speakers of languages from all over the world. If you are not so confident it will be a great opportunity for you to practise your English in real-world situations, not just describing your family to your teacher! You will be able to chat to your peers face to face during our weekly discussions, and also complete written assignments and social interactions on our Facebook page. No need to be nervous, if you can comfortably understand this FAQ you should be all right in our class.
					<br /><br />
					<b>How will I be assessed?</b><br />
					Don’t worry, you won’t have to sit any exams. At Online UWC we will not give you any multiple choice questions! We want to challenge you and help you grow as thinkers and problem-solvers for the world. We’ll do this through our unique program, which is based primarily on encouraging active participation and completion of class assignments (we require you to attend 3 out of 5 group sessions and complete 3 out of 5 assignments, as well as the final project which you will be asked to implement in your local community.
					<br /><br />
					<b>How do I sign up?</b><br />
					Go to our student <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1AyhbRDJYxeWACifHjKVe1IkVX1BqxxJasAE7SJkk4wk/viewform">sign up form</a>! You will be able to pay via our <a href="https://www.paypal.com/uk/cgi-bin/webscr?cmd=_flow&SESSION=kgGIg5oJkn0HW5l32BPpfRYYKTUzaum82hyNJpH4D_K1cfGRBiJBBCG1v6q&dispatch=50a222a57771920b6a3d7b606239e4d529b525e0b7e69bf0224adecfb0124e9b61f737ba21b081987669d951670e57a34adba9dd19029ce5">PayPal link</a>.
					<br /><br />
					<b>How much does it cost?</b><br />
					The cost for the 5-week Online UWC programme running from March 3 2014 - April 3rd is 15 GBP. Online UWC is a not for profit short course (and we spend the proceed from the course to cover the basic costs for running this course, including marketing and software development, though we aim to return at least 20% of the course proceeds back to the UWC community). If you would like to attend this course, but your parents do not have 15 GBP to spare, please do apply and let us know in your application that you would like to apply for financial aid.

					<br />
					<br />

			</p>
