			<h1>MENTORS</h1>
		</div>
		<div class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">
			<p class="right_msg">
				<b>Who can sign up to be a mentor for Online UWC?</b><br />
				Any UWC or university/college graduate with an interest in sustainability is welcome to apply to be a mentor. Also, if you have graduated from a previous edition of Online UWC course you are also eligible to apply to be a mentor (contact hanna[at]onlineuwc.org).
				<br /><br />
				<b>What exactly does being a mentor entail?</b><br />
				There are a number of ways you can help as mentor for Online UWC. You can:
				Help us build the curriculum. This is done prior to the start of the course.
				Volunteer as an expert lecturer (or help us find one) for a topic. This involves giving a 20-30 minute presentation followed by 30-40 mins of questions from and discussion with students.
				During the 5 week course, facilitate the weekly group session, which is held the day after the video lecture. This lasts for an hour. Your role is more of a chair, steering the discussion in the right direction and announcing the week’s assignment.
				A combination of any or all of the above
				<br /><br />
				<b>What is the time commitment for me as a mentor?</b><br />
				Depending on your role and how much you want to be involved this can be anything upwards of one hour a week. We are very flexible and try to do as much as we can for mentors to be able to fit their volunteering around their busy schedules.
				<br /><br />
				<b>How do I sign up?</b><br />
				The easiest way is to get in touch directly with hanna[at]onlineuwc.org. 
				<br /><br />
				<b>Does it cost anything?</b><br />
				No. You are already contributing a huge amount to the students and we thank you for that!
				<br /><br />
				<b>What do I get in return?</b><br />
				A chance to meet, work with and challenge an enthusiastic and idealistic group of students from around the world. A chance to be involved with a groundbreaking development in online education. The mentors come from several different fields and are a great team to work with. You get the chance to volunteer with a great educational initiative which helps spread the UWC values from the comfort of your home.
				<br /><br />
				<b>Do I have to have a connection with UWC?</b><br />
				Not at all. We welcome any volunteers with the will and knowledge to help our course be a success. Some knowledge of the <a href="http://uwc.org/about_uwc/default.aspx">UWC movement</a> is useful to know the background behind the Online UWC but is not necessary.

					<br />
					<br />

			</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>
