			<h1>TECHNOLOGY</h1>
		</div>
		<div class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">
			<p class="right_msg">
<b>What technology will I need?</b><br />
You will need a computer with access to the internet, a webcam, microphone and headphones. To access the video lectures and discussions you should have a high-speed internet connection.
See our <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1LrDmULRgSbNHdyZWtTQHdLWrg_VwmHt8KdxtEm8TZ2w/edit">Setting Up page</a> for more information and how to test your internet connection.
<br />
					<br />
<b>Do I need to download any software?</b><br />
Not really. All the software we use is free and available on the internet. You will need a Google account (sign up for one free here). If you don’t have an @gmail.com email account you can keep your email address (e.g. with @live.com, @outlook.com or @yahoo.com) but create a linked Google account here. 
You will also need a Facebook account since most of our non-class discussion will take place on Facebook.
The one thing you possibly need to download, if you don’t have it already, is Google’s free Talk browser extension/plug-in, which allows you to run Google Hangouts. This is the video programme, similar to Skype, which we use to hold the video lectures and group discussions. Click on <a href="https://www.google.com/hangouts/">this link</a> to download the Google Talk browser extension/plug-in and click on “Available for your computer”.
<br />
					<br />
<b>I don’t have my own computer. Is that ok?</b><br />
Yes, that’s fine. As long as you have access to a computer with a relatively good internet connection, webcam, microphone and headphones then you should have no problems taking part in the course.


					<br />
					<br />

			</p>
			</div>
		</div>
